 and consider the function 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}:\left(0,1\right)\to\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 be defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f^{-1}\left(x\right)=\tan\left(\pi x-\frac{\pi}{2}\right),
\]

\end_inset

then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
f^{-1}\circ f\left(x\right) & =f^{-1}\left(f\left(x\right)\right)\\
 & =\tan\left(\pi\left(\frac{\arctan\left(x\right)+\frac{\pi}{2}}{\pi}\right)-\frac{\pi}{2}\right)\\
 & =\tan\left(\arctan\left(x\right)+\frac{\pi}{2}-\frac{\pi}{2}\right)\\
 & =x,
\end{align*}

\end_inset

thus 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}$
\end_inset

 is the inverse function of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
 This means that 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is bijective.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is bijective, 
