According to Theorem 29.3, the Cartesian product of two countably infinite
 sets is again countably infinite, and according to Corollary 29.7.
 The set 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Q}$
\end_inset

 is countably infinite.
 Therefore, 
\begin_inset Formula $\abs{\mathbb{Z}\times\mathbb{N}}=\abs{\mathbb{Q}}$
